    "instruction": "Using metric.csv, for the incident window March 12, 2021 23:30:00 to March 13, 2021 00:00:00 (UTC+8), analyze only these components: IG01, IG02, MG01, MG02, Tomcat02, Tomcat03, Tomcat04, apache01, apache02, Mysql01, Mysql02, Redis01. For each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) do the following:\n1) Use the previously computed global P95 for that (cmdb_id,kpi_name) (calculate from the full series if not already available).\n2) Mark a point in the window as anomalous if value >= global_P95 (for KPIs where high is bad). Ignore KPIs with global_p95==0 for severity ratio calculation but still detect consecutive non-zero runs (report global_p95==0 accordingly).\n3) Identify consecutive anomalous sub-series with minimum length 2 (consecutive timestamps). For each sub-series, compute start_ts, end_ts, length_in_points, max_value_in_segment, severity_ratio = max_value_in_segment / global_p95 (handle divide-by-zero).\nReturn compact results (limit 20 rows) aggregated per (cmdb_id,kpi_name) with: cmdb_id, kpi_name, segments_count, earliest_segment_start_ts, earliest_segment_end_ts, earliest_segment_length, max_segment_severity_ratio. Also return up to 10 sample segments (one row per sample segment) with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, segment_start_ts, segment_end_ts, length, max_value, severity_ratio. Store full intermediate tables in kernel variables but only return the compact tables and sample segments."
